item.title: LimeZ - Zero [Chill, Trap, Dubstep] (Any feedback?)
item.dc:creator: therealejoc
item.description:
Overall a good song. The beginning was a little slow. And I think there was maybe a little to much reverb on the drums, at least for an intro/buildup (my opinion of course). Once the drop hit it was super good! Love the feel of it and the transition also was very nice. Melodically a pretty solid song, enjoyable to listen to for most of it. Idk how chill I would consider it though. For me chill is more of a mellow type of song but that’s once again an opinion thing. Thanks for sharing, hope to hear more!
